This was my first experience with Ethiopian food.
I went there with a group of 12 ladies.
Our waiter was very attentive and friendly.
He even turned down the music so our large group could hear each other.
The food was really delicious.
You use bread to pick up the meat and vegetables, which is kind of sour with a slight vinegar flavor, which I loved.
